# ProbeScan — Professional Penetration Testing Framework

## Stack (never deviate)
- Backend: Rust via Tauri 2.x
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite (inside Tauri webview)
- Storage: SQLite via sqlx with migrations
- External tools: tokio::process::Command async subprocesses
- Styling: CSS custom properties, JetBrains Mono + Syne fonts
- No CLI interface, no plugin system, no proxy

## Rust Conventions
- All Tauri commands: `#[tauri::command] async fn name() -> Result<T, String>`
- Convert errors with `.map_err(|e| e.to_string())`
- Stream subprocess stdout via Tauri events: `app_handle.emit("event", payload)`
- State managed via `tauri::State<Mutex<AppState>>`
- All DB access through `db::` module functions
- Use `uuid::Uuid::new_v4().to_string()` for all IDs

## React Conventions  
- Functional components + hooks only
- All API calls via `invoke()` from `@tauri-apps/api/core`
- Listen to streaming events via `listen()` from `@tauri-apps/api/event`
- Types defined in `src/types/index.ts`
- Dark theme only — CSS variables defined in `src/index.css`
- No external UI libraries — custom components only

## Vulnerability Schema (always use this exact shape)
```typescript
interface VulnFinding {
  id: string;
  scan_id: string;
  source_tool: string;
  severity: 'CRITICAL' | 'HIGH' | 'MEDIUM' | 'LOW' | 'INFO';
  title: string;
  description: string;
  affected_url: string;
  affected_port: number | null;
  cve_references: string[];
  cvss_score: number | null;
  evidence: string;
  remediation: string;
  timestamp: string;
  in_scope: boolean;
}
```

## Tool Integration Rules
- subfinder: JSON output (`-oJ`), passive + CT logs
- feroxbuster: JSON output (`--json`)
- katana: JSON output (`-json`)
- nmap: XML output → parse with roxmltree
- nuclei: JSONL output (`-json`)
- testssl.sh: JSON output (`--jsonfile`)
- whatweb: JSON output (`--log-json`)
- ALL tools must support non-interactive execution
- Scope check ALWAYS happens in Rust before active scan

## File Structure
```
src-tauri/src/
  main.rs          — Tauri setup, command registration
  commands/        — One file per feature area
  db/              — All SQLite operations
  scanner/         — Subprocess runner, scope engine
  parsers/         — One parser per tool
src/
  components/tabs/ — One component per tab
  components/ui/   — Shared UI primitives
  hooks/           — Custom React hooks
  types/           — TypeScript types
  lib/             — tauri invoke wrappers
```
